org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.ltl

Class LTLUnary

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.Logic
      • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.ltl.LTL
        • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.ltl.LTLUnary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, NegationNormalForm<LTL>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LTLAlways, LTLBefore, LTLNegation, LTLNext, LTLOnce, LTLPrevious, LTLSofar, LTLSometime

    public abstract class LTLUnary
extends LTL
    This class represents LTL formulae obtained by applying a unary operator to a LTL formula, for example, "~ f", "() f", "<> f", "[] f", "(-) f", "(~) f", "<-> f", and "[-] f".
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai
    See Also:
